Sentencas: Cobalt-free perovskites, Ln(0.5)Sr(0.5)Pe(0.8)Cu(0.2)O(3-delta) (Ln = La, Pr, and Nd), are systematically evaluated as the cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) using Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 as the electrolyte.
Titulo: Systematic evaluation of cobalt-free Ln0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ (Ln = La, Pr, and Nd) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The samples exhibit an orthorhombic perovskite structures, and their cell volumes decrease as the ionic radius of Ln decreases.
Titulo: Systematic evaluation of cobalt-free Ln0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ (Ln = La, Pr, and Nd) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Both the oxygen vacancy content and the magnitude of lattice oxygen release per formula unit increase in the temperature range from 370 degrees C to 850 degrees C as the ionic radius of Ln decreases.
Titulo: Systematic evaluation of cobalt-free Ln0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ (Ln = La, Pr, and Nd) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ln(0.5)Sr(0.5)Fe(0.8)Cu(0.2)O(3-delta) is chemically and thermally compatible with the Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 electrolyte.
Titulo: Systematic evaluation of cobalt-free Ln0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ (Ln = La, Pr, and Nd) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In the temperature range of 600 degrees C-750 degrees C, Nd0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-delta possesses the highest catalytic activity for the oxygen reduction reaction with area specific resistance values of 0.071 Omega cm(2) and 0.141 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Systematic evaluation of cobalt-free Ln0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ (Ln = La, Pr, and Nd) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power densities of the anode-supported single cells at 800 degrees C and 700 degrees C are 1003.7 mW cm(-2) and 516.7 mW cm(-2) for Pr0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-delta and 944.5 mW cm(-2) and 530.2 mW cm(-2) for Nd0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-delta, respectively.
Titulo: Systematic evaluation of cobalt-free Ln0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ (Ln = La, Pr, and Nd) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ln(0.5)Sr(0.5)Fe(0.8)Cu(0.2)O(3-delta) is shown to be a promising cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Systematic evaluation of cobalt-free Ln0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ (Ln = La, Pr, and Nd) as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
